<section class="py-20 px-6 border-b border-theme-border">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-theme-primary mb-4">
        Terminal-based AI workflows don't scale
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-theme-primary/50">
        If you're working on multiple projects, you've hit these walls.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="pain-point">
        <div class="pain-icon">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2" ry="2"/>
            <line x1="8" y1="21" x2="16" y2="21"/>
            <line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12" y2="21"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="pain-title">Context switching nightmare</h3>
          <p class="pain-desc">Which terminal has which project? Which agent is waiting for input? You're constantly hunting.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pain-point">
        <div class="pain-icon">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M12 22c5.523 0 10-4.477 10-10S17.523 2 12 2 2 6.477 2 12s4.477 10 10 10z"/>
            <path d="M12 6v6l4 2"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="pain-title">Agents waiting in the background</h3>
          <p class="pain-desc">An agent needs your approval but you forgot about it. Tasks stall because you can't see what's pending.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pain-point">
        <div class="pain-icon">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <rect x="9" y="9" width="13" height="13" rx="2" ry="2"/>
            <path d="M5 15H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h9a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v1"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="pain-title">Copy-paste hell</h3>
          <p class="pain-desc">Terminal selection is a trap. Scrollback disappears. You can't easily grab code snippets or errors.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pain-point">
        <div class="pain-icon">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
            <path d="M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3"/>
            <line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="pain-title">Lost track of what happened where</h3>
          <p class="pain-desc">Was that bugfix in project A or B? Terminals don't give you history you can actually search.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-center text-theme-primary/40 mt-10 text-sm">
      Molt Code solves this with a proper workspaceâ€”not another terminal wrapper.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .pain-point {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .pain-icon {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 2.5rem;
    height: 2.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1);
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    color: #f87171;
  }

  .pain-title {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .pain-desc {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-secondary);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
</style>
